Element AbstractAppearance

AbstractAppearance is the abstract superclass to represent any kind of appearance objects.

Element adeOfAbstractAppearance

Augments AbstractAppearance with properties defined in an ADE.

Element AbstractCityObject

AbstractCityObject is the abstract superclass of all thematic classes within the CityGML Conceptual Model.

Element externalReference

References external objects in other information systems that have a relation to the city object.

Element generalizesTo

Relates generalized representations of the same real-world object in different Levels of Detail to the city object. The direction of this relation is from the city object to the corresponding generalized city objects.

Application Data

<targetElement>
core:AbstractCityObject
</targetElement>

Element relativeToTerrain

Describes the vertical position of the city object relative to the surrounding terrain.

Element relativeToWater

Describes the vertical position of the city object relative to the surrounding water surface.

Element appearance

Relates appearances to the city object.

Element genericAttribute

Relates generic attributes to the city object.

Element dynamizer

Relates Dynamizer objects to the city object. These allow timeseries data to override static attribute values of the city object.

Element adeOfAbstractCityObject

Augments AbstractCityObject with properties defined in an ADE.

Element AbstractDynamizer

AbstractDynamizer is the abstract superclass to represent Dynamizer objects.

Element adeOfAbstractDynamizer

Augments AbstractDynamizer with properties defined in an ADE.

Element AbstractFeature

AbstractFeature is the abstract superclass of all feature types within the CityGML Conceptual Model.

Element adeOfAbstractFeature

Augments AbstractFeature with properties defined in an ADE.

Element AbstractFeatureWithLifespan

AbstractFeatureWithLifespan is the base class for all CityGML features. This class allows the optional specification of the real-world and database times for the existence of each feature.

Element creationDate

Indicates the date at which a CityGML feature was added to the CityModel.

Element terminationDate

Indicates the date at which a CityGML feature was removed from the CityModel.

Element validFrom

Indicates the date at which a CityGML feature started to exist in the real world.

Element validTo

Indicates the date at which a CityGML feature ended to exist in the real world.

Element adeOfAbstractFeatureWithLifespan

Augments AbstractFeatureWithLifespan with properties defined in an ADE.

Element AbstractGenericAttribute

AbstractGenericAttribute is the abstract superclass for all types of generic attributes.

Element AbstractLogicalSpace

AbstractLogicalSpace is the abstract superclass for all types of logical spaces. Logical space refers to spaces that are not bounded by physical surfaces but are defined according to thematic considerations.

Element adeOfAbstractLogicalSpace

Augments AbstractLogicalSpace with properties defined in an ADE.

Element AbstractOccupiedSpace

AbstractOccupiedSpace is the abstract superclass for all types of physically occupied spaces. Occupied space refers to spaces that are partially or entirely filled with matter.

Element lod1ImplicitRepresentation

Relates to an implicit geometry that represents the occupied space in Level of Detail 1.

Element lod2ImplicitRepresentation

Relates to an implicit geometry that represents the occupied space in Level of Detail 2.

Element lod3ImplicitRepresentation

Relates to an implicit geometry that represents the occupied space in Level of Detail 3.

Element adeOfAbstractOccupiedSpace

Augments AbstractOccupiedSpace with properties defined in an ADE.

Element AbstractPhysicalSpace

AbstractPhysicalSpace is the abstract superclass for all types of physical spaces. Physical space refers to spaces that are fully or partially bounded by physical objects.

Element lod1TerrainIntersectionCurve

Relates to a 3D MultiCurve geometry that represents the terrain intersection curve of the physical space in Level of Detail 1.

Element lod2TerrainIntersectionCurve

Relates to a 3D MultiCurve geometry that represents the terrain intersection curve of the physical space in Level of Detail 2.

Element lod3TerrainIntersectionCurve

Relates to a 3D MultiCurve geometry that represents the terrain intersection curve of the physical space in Level of Detail 3.

Element pointCloud

Relates to a 3D PointCloud that represents the physical space.

Element adeOfAbstractPhysicalSpace

Augments AbstractPhysicalSpace with properties defined in an ADE.

Element AbstractPointCloud

AbstractPointCloud is the abstract superclass to represent PointCloud objects.

Element adeOfAbstractPointCloud

Augments AbstractPointCloud with properties defined in an ADE.

Element AbstractSpace

AbstractSpace is the abstract superclass for all types of spaces. A space is an entity of volumetric extent in the real world.

Element spaceType

Specifies the degree of openness of a space.

Element volume

Specifies qualified volumes related to the space.

Element area

Specifies qualified areas related to the space.

Element boundary

Relates to surfaces that bound the space.

Element lod0Point

Relates to a 3D Point geometry that represents the space in Level of Detail 0.

Element lod0MultiSurface

Relates to a 3D MultiSurface geometry that represents the space in Level of Detail 0.

Element lod0MultiCurve

Relates to a 3D MultiCurve geometry that represents the space in Level of Detail 0.

Element lod1Solid

Relates to a 3D Solid geometry that represents the space in Level of Detail 1.

Element lod2Solid

Relates to a 3D Solid geometry that represents the space in Level of Detail 2.

Element lod2MultiSurface

Relates to a 3D MultiSurface geometry that represents the space in Level of Detail 2.

Element lod2MultiCurve

Relates to a 3D MultiCurve geometry that represents the space in Level of Detail 2.

Element lod3Solid

Relates to a 3D Solid geometry that represents the space in Level of Detail 3.

Element lod3MultiSurface

Relates to a 3D MultiSurface geometry that represents the space in Level of Detail 3.

Element lod3MultiCurve

Relates to a 3D MultiCurve geometry that represents the space in Level of Detail 3.

Element adeOfAbstractSpace

Augments AbstractSpace with properties defined in an ADE.

Element AbstractSpaceBoundary

AbstractSpaceBoundary is the abstract superclass for all types of space boundaries. A space boundary is an entity with areal extent in the real world. Space boundaries are objects that bound a Space. They also realize the contact between adjacent spaces.

Element adeOfAbstractSpaceBoundary

Augments AbstractSpaceBoundary with properties defined in an ADE.

Element AbstractThematicSurface

AbstractThematicSurface is the abstract superclass for all types of thematic surfaces.

Element area

Specifies qualified areas related to the thematic surface.

Element lod0MultiCurve

Relates to a 3D MultiCurve geometry that represents the thematic surface in Level of Detail 0.

Element lod0MultiSurface

Relates to a 3D MultiSurface geometry that represents the thematic surface in Level of Detail 0.

Element lod1MultiSurface

Relates to a 3D MultiSurface geometry that represents the thematic surface in Level of Detail 1.

Element lod2MultiSurface

Relates to a 3D MultiSurface geometry that represents the thematic surface in Level of Detail 2.

Element lod3MultiSurface

Relates to a 3D MultiSurface geometry that represents the thematic surface in Level of Detail 3.

Element pointCloud

Relates to a 3D PointCloud that represents the thematic surface.

Element adeOfAbstractThematicSurface

Augments AbstractThematicSurface with properties defined in an ADE.

Element AbstractUnoccupiedSpace

AbstractUnoccupiedSpace is the abstract superclass for all types of physically unoccupied spaces. Unoccupied space refers to spaces that are entirely or mostly free of matter.

Element adeOfAbstractUnoccupiedSpace

Augments AbstractUnoccupiedSpace with properties defined in an ADE.

Element AbstractVersion

AbstractVersion is the abstract superclass to represent Version objects.

Element adeOfAbstractVersion

Augments AbstractVersion with properties defined in an ADE.

Element AbstractVersionTransition

AbstractVersionTransition is the abstract superclass to represent VersionTransition objects.

Element adeOfAbstractVersionTransition

Augments AbstractVersionTransition with properties defined in an ADE.

Element Address

Address represents an address of a city object.

Element xalAddress

Relates an OASIS address object to the Address.

Element multiPoint

Relates to the MultiPoint geometry of the Address. The geometry relates the address spatially to a city object.

Element adeOfAddress

Augments the Address with properties defined in an ADE.

Element CityModel

CityModel is the container for all objects belonging to a city model.

Element engineeringCRS

Specifies the local engineering coordinate reference system of the CityModel that can be provided inline the CityModel instead of referencing a well-known CRS definition. The definition of an engineering CRS requires an anchor point which relates the origin of the local coordinate system to a point on the earth’s surface in order to facilitate the transformation of coordinates from the local engineering CRS.

Element adeOfCityModel

Augments the CityModel with properties defined in an ADE.

Element cityObjectMember

Specifies the city objects that are part of the CityModel.

Element appearanceMember

Specifies the appearances of the CityModel.

Element versionMember

Specifies the different versions of the CityModel.

Element versionTransitionMember

Specifies the transitions between the different versions of the CityModel.

Element featureMember

Specifies the feature objects that are part of the CityModel. It allows to include objects that are not derived from a class defined in the CityGML conceptual model, but from the ISO 19109 class AnyFeature.

Element CityObjectRelation

CityObjectRelation represents a specific relation from the city object in which the relation is included to another city object.

Element genericAttribute

Relates generic attributes to the CityObjectRelation.

Element ClosureSurface

ClosureSurface is a special type of thematic surface used to close holes in volumetric objects. Closure surfaces are virtual (non-physical) surfaces.

Element adeOfClosureSurface

Augments the ClosureSurface with properties defined in an ADE.

Simple Type DoubleBetween0and1Type

DoubleBetween0and1 is a basic type for values, which are greater or equal than 0 and less or equal than 1. The type is used for color encoding, for example.

Simple Type DoubleBetween0and1ListType

DoubleBetween0and1List is a basic type that represents a list of double values greater or equal than 0 and less or equal than 1. The type is used for color encoding, for example.

Element ExternalReference

ExternalReference is a reference to a corresponding object in another information system, for example in the German cadastre (ALKIS), the German topographic information system (ATKIS), or the OS UK MasterMap®.

Element targetResource

Specifies the URI that points to the object in the external information system.

Element informationSystem

Specifies the URI that points to the external information system.

Element relationType

Specifies a URI that additionally qualifies the ExternalReference. The URI can point to a definition from an external ontology (e.g. the sameAs relation from OWL) and allows for mapping the ExternalReference to RDF triples.

Element ImplicitGeometry

ImplicitGeometry is a geometry representation where the shape is stored only once as a prototypical geometry. Examples are a tree or other vegetation object, a traffic light or a traffic sign. This prototypic geometry object can be re-used or referenced many times, wherever the corresponding feature occurs in the 3D city model.

Element transformationMatrix

Specifies the mathematical transformation (translation, rotation, and scaling) between the prototypical geometry and the actual spatial position of the object.

Element mimeType

Specifies the MIME type of the external file that stores the prototypical geometry.

Element libraryObject

Specifies the URI that points to the prototypical geometry stored in an external file.

Element referencePoint

Relates to a 3D Point geometry that represents the base point of the object in the world coordinate system.

Element relativeGeometry

Relates to a prototypical geometry in a local coordinate system stored inline with the city model.

Element appearance

Relates appearances to the ImplicitGeometry.

Simple Type IntegerBetween0and3Type

IntegerBetween0and3 is a basic type for integer values, which are greater or equal than 0 and less or equal than 3. The type is used for encoding the LOD number.

Element Occupancy

Occupancy is an application-dependent indication of what is contained by a feature.

Element numberOfOccupants

Indicates the number of occupants contained by a feature.

Element interval

Indicates the time period the occupants are contained by a feature.

Element occupantType

Indicates the specific type of the occupants that are contained by a feature.

Element QualifiedArea

QualifiedArea is an application-dependent measure of the area of a space or of a thematic surface.

Element area

Specifies the value of the QualifiedArea.

Element typeOfArea

Indicates the specific type of the QualifiedArea.

Element QualifiedVolume

QualifiedVolume is an application-dependent measure of the volume of a space.

Element volume

Specifies the value of the QualifiedVolume.

Element typeOfVolume

Indicates the specific type of the QualifiedVolume.

Simple Type RelativeToTerrainType

RelativeToTerrain enumerates the spatial relations of a city object relative to terrain in a qualitative way.

Simple Type RelativeToWaterType

RelativeToWater enumerates the spatial relations of a city object relative to the water surface in a qualitative way.

Simple Type SpaceTypeType

SpaceType is an enumeration that characterises a space according to its closure properties.

Simple Type TransformationMatrix2x2Type

TransformationMatrix2x2 is a 2 by 2 matrix represented as a list of four double values in row major order.

Simple Type TransformationMatrix3x4Type

TransformationMatrix3x4 is a 3 by 4 matrix represented as a list of twelve double values in row major order.

Simple Type TransformationMatrix4x4Type

TransformationMatrix4x4 is a 4 by 4 matrix represented as a list of sixteen double values in row major order.

Documentation
The Core module defines the basic components of the CityGML conceptual model. This includes abstract base classes that define the core properties of more specialized thematic classes defined in other modules as well as concrete classes that are common to other modules, for example basic data types.

Glossary

Abstract (Applies to complex type definitions and element declarations). An abstract element or complex type cannot used to validate an element instance. If there is a reference to an abstract element, only element declarations that can substitute the abstract element can be used to validate the instance. For references to abstract type definitions, only derived types can be used.

All Model Group Child elements can be provided in any order in instances. See: http://www.w3.org/TR/xmlschema-1/#element-all.

Choice Model Group Only one from the list of child elements and model groups can be provided in instances. See: http://www.w3.org/TR/xmlschema-1/#element-choice.

Collapse Whitespace Policy Replace tab, line feed, and carriage return characters with space character (Unicode character 32). Then, collapse contiguous sequences of space characters into single space character, and remove leading and trailing space characters.

Disallowed Substitutions (Applies to element declarations). If substitution is specified, then substitution group members cannot be used in place of the given element declaration to validate element instances. If derivation methods, e.g. extension, restriction, are specified, then the given element declaration will not validate element instances that have types derived from the element declaration's type using the specified derivation methods. Normally, element instances can override their declaration's type by specifying an xsi:type attribute.

Key Constraint Like Uniqueness Constraint, but additionally requires that the specified value(s) must be provided. See: http://www.w3.org/TR/xmlschema-1/#cIdentity-constraint_Definitions.

Key Reference Constraint Ensures that the specified value(s) must match value(s) from a Key Constraint or Uniqueness Constraint. See: http://www.w3.org/TR/xmlschema-1/#cIdentity-constraint_Definitions.

Model Group Groups together element content, specifying the order in which the element content can occur and the number of times the group of element content may be repeated. See: http://www.w3.org/TR/xmlschema-1/#Model_Groups.

Nillable (Applies to element declarations). If an element declaration is nillable, instances can use the xsi:nil attribute. The xsi:nil attribute is the boolean attribute, nil, from the http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance namespace. If an element instance has an xsi:nil attribute set to true, it can be left empty, even though its element declaration may have required content.

Notation A notation is used to identify the format of a piece of data. Values of elements and attributes that are of type, NOTATION, must come from the names of declared notations. See: http://www.w3.org/TR/xmlschema-1/#cNotation_Declarations.

Preserve Whitespace Policy Preserve whitespaces exactly as they appear in instances.

Prohibited Derivations (Applies to type definitions). Derivation methods that cannot be used to create sub-types from a given type definition.

Prohibited Substitutions (Applies to complex type definitions). Prevents sub-types that have been derived using the specified derivation methods from validating element instances in place of the given type definition.

Replace Whitespace Policy Replace tab, line feed, and carriage return characters with space character (Unicode character 32).

Sequence Model Group Child elements and model groups must be provided in the specified order in instances. See: http://www.w3.org/TR/xmlschema-1/#element-sequence.

Substitution Group Elements that are members of a substitution group can be used wherever the head element of the substitution group is referenced.

Substitution Group Exclusions (Applies to element declarations). Prohibits element declarations from nominating themselves as being able to substitute a given element declaration, if they have types that are derived from the original element's type using the specified derivation methods.

Target Namespace The target namespace identifies the namespace that components in this schema belongs to. If no target namespace is provided, then the schema components do not belong to any namespace.

Uniqueness Constraint Ensures uniqueness of an element/attribute value, or a combination of values, within a specified scope. See: http://www.w3.org/TR/xmlschema-1/#cIdentity-constraint_Definitions.
